          <p class='first-para'>
            The report quoted Mr. Edwards:
            <q>'I come from a racist culture in Cardiff and now that I live in Aberaeron and work in Lampeter I know children who are discriminated against because they are English,' he said. He said his son Nick, brought up fluent in Welsh, was so disgusted with
            
            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_63wh' title='Col. 63WH &mdash; HC Deb 07 May 2002 vol 385 c63WH' name='column_63wh' href='#column_63wh' rel='bookmark'>63WH</a>
            the attitudes he found among Welsh speakers towards English that now, at the age of 30, he wants nothing to do with the Welsh language.</q>
            That is extremely sad. I want the Welsh language saved and I want it to flourish. I call upon the Welsh nationalist party today to unite the communities of Wales&#x2014;to unite the Welsh speakers and the English speakers, so that we have one Welsh nation.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
